<paragraph id="A3C4030F27BC10A58A32990B74BAF783" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9349BEA94A077BAF06AE0D35A5E71173" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="5B8EFE397427AF9BCBDB1EA624901351" authorityName="Cobos-Villagran, R. Valenz. &amp; Raymundo" authorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Hysteriaceae" genus="Rhytidhysteron" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhytidhysteron esperanzae" order="Patellariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="esperanzae">
<emphasis id="E4EDAC9BC57CD00C9E37AE7F1A1BA249" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Rhytidhysteron esperanzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is characterised by a brown, dull-green to black exciple and dark green to black epithecium that, in reaction with 10% KOH, changes to yellow colouration. This colouration with KOH is very different than those of of 
<taxonomicName id="5A7EA4EEFBC8E6080B006AEA3978BE84" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. rufulum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufulum">
<emphasis id="C60593F607BE630F11B8098B66B4746E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. rufulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5513E35292C2967478D0AEF9A6539C29" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. neorufulum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neorufulum">
<emphasis id="5F7E0844DC907333470783D1BDF2AD62" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. neorufulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which are magenta and violet, respectively. 
<taxonomicName id="CD1C006584723305C8F7C261C3113FA6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. esperanzae" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esperanzae">
<emphasis id="1F29E34B9BF615A1CC0096DE0DA8EBAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. esperanzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have larger ascospores than 
<taxonomicName id="D791ED52C2FC43005AF3E99733834CC4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. rufulum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufulum">
<emphasis id="AD508601EA84146CB8FAA69D586AFF3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. rufulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(22.4-30.4 
<normalizedToken id="9BE5F6CF2D08C706B64DA098096368E1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9.6 
<normalizedToken id="54177CC0456398F51F8A21A2A5537F8C" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="E985C11517456C3AABA229B2DCF6663F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. mexicanum" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="EE6449E70C1A43C5E311E6D539EA1FB5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">R. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(34-40 
<normalizedToken id="DFC898B31BEFF0421016E664870C39CC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-12 
<normalizedToken id="7283533DAB4CD800F908B5B8DBA40B2B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). Ecologically, this new species grows in a tropical cloud forest dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="620DAD1CD5ED1D8F53CDA533B0C8CD55" authorityName="J.-F.Leroy" authorityYear="1951" baseAuthorityName="Standl.J.-F.Leroy" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Oreomunnea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oreomunnea mexicana" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis id="21A34B701B9B582FFB6E29ACA04DB3BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Oreomunnea mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Standl. J.-F. Leroy (
<taxonomicName id="9CC80D65A7A9BDAC1B95172A3A89295D" authorityName="Oersted" authorityYear="1856" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Oreomunnea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Juglandaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
